07/11/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- US Secretary of State Colin Powell reiterated his country's commitment to supporting and assisting Macedonia's development. In a letter sent Tuesday (5 November) to Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva, Powell noted Macedonia's significant steps toward stabilisation and recovery, and urged the new government to focus efforts on transforming the country into a fully integrated and prosperous member of the international security system.
In other news, Macedonia's army began destroying some 22,800 PMR-2A anti-infantry mines at the Krivolak military base Wednesday. By the end of February, nearly 43,000 will be destroyed under the 1999 Ottawa Convention. (Utrinski Vesnik - 07/11/02; Makfax, A1 TV, BBC, MIA- 06/11/02)
